01:01:37.460 --> 01:01:38.760
Like, what's going on?

01:01:38.760 --> 01:01:40.060
I was like I just --

01:01:40.060 --> 01:01:42.700
it's a story, there
was a joke [laughter].

01:01:42.700 --> 01:01:45.410
And, so, I think -- I think
the two can be played off

01:01:45.410 --> 01:01:48.240
against each other in
very effective ways.

01:01:50.490 --> 01:01:51.790
&gt;&gt; Gowri K.: We had
a question up here

01:01:51.790 --> 01:01:54.090
in this second row, Anne.

01:01:55.410 --> 01:01:56.720
&gt;&gt; Okay, this is a question --

01:01:56.720 --> 01:02:00.560
well, a comment and
a question for Reese.

01:02:00.560 --> 01:02:03.770
So, I was having lunch, and
I'm so glad that you ended

01:02:03.770 --> 01:02:05.820
with that comment
about obsession

01:02:05.820 --> 01:02:08.620
and your writing
process and how you sort

01:02:08.620 --> 01:02:10.050
of wrote everything
over and over again.

01:02:10.050 --> 01:02:15.140
And I, as a reader of your work
anyway, really appreciate that.

01:02:15.140 --> 01:02:17.660
And I was at lunch today
with a bunch of writers

01:02:17.660 --> 01:02:21.310
who actually do crime fiction,
things like that, and I

01:02:21.310 --> 01:02:23.820
was talking about how I was
coming to this event tonight

01:02:23.820 --> 01:02:27.050
and I was excited and
how it's very short.

01:02:27.050 --> 01:02:33.230
But, I feel like you must have
started like an 800-page novel

01:02:33.230 --> 01:02:39.250
and then like over eight years
[inaudible] it taken you.

01:02:39.250 --> 01:02:42.770
And you had sort of compressed
it down and sort of taken

01:02:42.770 --> 01:02:46.760
out every fluff word,
answer taken,

01:02:46.760 --> 01:02:50.670
like every eight word sentence
and made it into four words

01:02:50.670 --> 01:02:52.190
until it meant the same thing

01:02:52.190 --> 01:02:54.160
and carried all the
same emotion,

01:02:54.160 --> 01:02:58.010
and just -- but, you made
it into this compressed,

01:02:58.010 --> 01:03:02.420
dense thing of emotion and
sort of beauty and rhythm

01:03:02.420 --> 01:03:05.430
and that it actually
took me a while

01:03:05.430 --> 01:03:06.730
to read just because I was --

01:03:06.730 --> 01:03:08.850
just I had to re-read
some of these sentences

01:03:08.850 --> 01:03:10.500
because they were
just so magnificent.

01:03:10.500 --> 01:03:13.610
So, as a reader, thank
you for taking that time,

01:03:13.610 --> 01:03:17.130
and those extra years, I
think, really shows up.

01:03:17.130 --> 01:03:19.800
So, anyway, so that's
my comment.

01:03:19.800 --> 01:03:25.050
The question is, as far as the
