01:03:35.190 --> 01:03:38.480
where she's telling the
story in her own words

01:03:38.480 --> 01:03:39.780
through recollection or Will,

01:03:39.780 --> 01:03:42.400
but I feel like they're
actually still Will's chapters

01:03:42.400 --> 01:03:47.080
and he's interpreting
for us what she,

01:03:47.080 --> 01:03:49.730
you know, told him
or a story about her

01:03:49.730 --> 01:03:51.080
that he recalls or whatever.

01:03:51.080 --> 01:03:54.400
Was that intentional
and have you --

01:03:54.400 --> 01:03:58.320
I'm just wondering if anybody
tried to [inaudible] hey,

01:03:58.320 --> 01:04:03.570
maybe we should, you know,
like take out that Will filter

01:04:03.570 --> 01:04:06.310
and just make it straight
Phoebe or whatever?

01:04:06.310 --> 01:04:08.660
I'm just curious.

01:04:08.660 --> 01:04:11.640
&gt;&gt; R. O. Kwon: So, as I
mentioned in my reading,

01:04:11.640 --> 01:04:13.530
the novel alternates
between three points of view,

01:04:13.530 --> 01:04:15.220
cult leader, Phoebe, and Will.

01:04:15.220 --> 01:04:19.060
And, in a lot of ways, I don't
think I'm giving too much away

01:04:19.060 --> 01:04:20.360
by noting that the

01:04:20.360 --> 01:04:22.170
novel does indicate
in a lot of ways

01:04:22.170 --> 01:04:24.350
that Will's the one really
telling the whole novel.

01:04:24.350 --> 01:04:28.670
And, so, the first two years
the novel was told entirely

01:04:28.670 --> 01:04:30.510
from Phoebe's point of view.

01:04:30.510 --> 01:04:34.160
And then I realized that, well,
so Phoebe goes through a lot.

01:04:34.160 --> 01:04:36.550
Like she -- again, I don't
think I'm giving too much away

01:04:36.550 --> 01:04:38.600
by that she loses a
lot and then she sort

01:04:38.600 --> 01:04:41.040
of gains a lot in some ways.

01:04:41.040 --> 01:04:43.840
And then she -- you know,
like she joins a radical cult

01:04:43.840 --> 01:04:46.950
and she is probably involved
in blowing up a building.

01:04:46.950 --> 01:04:48.250
Like there's just like --

01:04:48.250 --> 01:04:51.040
there's a lot of lived
life experience there.

01:04:51.040 --> 01:04:55.470
And it became claustrophobic for
me to remain just in her head.

01:04:55.470 --> 01:04:59.010
And I was thinking a lot
about The Great Gatsby

01:04:59.010 --> 01:05:01.490
and the Nick Carraway
with the novel [inaudible]

01:05:01.490 --> 01:05:03.220
by having him narrate the novel

01:05:03.220 --> 01:05:06.330
versus pretty much
anyone else in the book.

01:05:06.330 --> 01:05:08.590
He's one of the most least of
all characters in a lot of ways

01:05:08.590 --> 01:05:09.890
in these characters' lives.

01:05:09.890 --> 01:05:12.700
And, so, I found that when I
stepped aside and let sort of --

01:05:12.700 --> 01:05:14.060
and let somebody
who loved Phoebe,

01:05:14.060 --> 01:05:16.830
but wasn't involved
very much in the act --

01:05:16.830 --> 01:05:19.730
in the sort of main action
of the book, tell the book,

01:05:19.730 --> 01:05:21.930
it opened up -- like
it opened up.

01:05:21.930 --> 01:05:23.230
It brought air into the room.

01:05:23.230 --> 01:05:26.240
It opened up a lot of
sort of space to play.

01:05:26.240 --> 01:05:27.740
So, there's that.

01:05:27.740 --> 01:05:30.630
The second question about
splitting up the book.

01:05:30.630 --> 01:05:31.930
So, I -- this is a question,

01:05:31.930 --> 01:05:34.190
and with first person
novels I know a lot

01:05:34.190 --> 01:05:36.040
of people don't have
any problem with this,

01:05:36.040 --> 01:05:40.050
but I found that I wanted the
novel to have a reason to exist,

01:05:40.050 --> 01:05:42.710
even inside of its
own fictional world.

01:05:42.710 --> 01:05:45.370
And, so, in some
ways the novel comes

01:05:45.370 --> 01:05:48.090
about because Will's trying
to understand what happened,

01:05:48.090 --> 01:05:50.970
what happened to this woman he
loved and what happened to him,

01:05:50.970 --> 01:05:52.270
what happened to
their relationship.

01:05:52.270 --> 01:05:55.130
And, so, that -- and
he's sort of trying to --

01:05:55.130 --> 01:05:56.430
he trying to understand.

01:05:56.430 --> 01:05:58.040
He's trying to explain it.

01:05:58.040 --> 01:06:02.350
And, so, that whole explanation
is -- that attempt is the book.

01:06:02.350 --> 01:06:05.470
And, so, the novel -- I
never wanted the novel,

01:06:05.470 --> 01:06:08.650
I found I never wanted
the novel to stray outside

01:06:08.650 --> 01:06:12.120
of what Will could either know
or imagine about what happened.

01:06:12.120 --> 01:06:14.470
And, so, that provided sort
of like a very useful circle

01:06:14.470 --> 01:06:16.450
around what was possible.

01:06:16.450 --> 01:06:19.210
So, all of this sounds
very intentional.

01:06:19.210 --> 01:06:20.510
It wasn't intentional
[laughter].

01:06:20.510 --> 01:06:21.810
Like I feel as though

01:06:21.810 --> 01:06:23.110
like nothing I did
was [inaudible] choose

01:06:23.110 --> 01:06:24.790
or decided [inaudible]
useable word.

01:06:24.790 --> 01:06:31.700
It was more like had to happen
after 50,000 revision attempts.

01:06:31.700 --> 01:06:35.080
It's like, oh okay, yeah, this
is what was supposed to happen.

01:06:35.080 --> 01:06:37.820
&gt;&gt; Gowri K.: I think we have
