Now I'm just calling
people by name.

01:06:43.670 --> 01:06:46.640
&gt;&gt; Thank you so much to
both of you for being here.

01:06:46.640 --> 01:06:51.070
I had a question about
writing [inaudible]

01:06:51.070 --> 01:06:56.180
and the actual discipline of

01:06:56.180 --> 01:06:59.550
sitting yourself down
and just, you know,

01:06:59.550 --> 01:07:03.280
unloading whatever you have
onto the page, the screen.

01:07:03.280 --> 01:07:07.840
And I've been trying
to find the balance

01:07:07.840 --> 01:07:10.620
between writing discipline
and practice

01:07:10.620 --> 01:07:13.040
and self-care, because I

01:07:13.040 --> 01:07:16.500
feel like as someone who
grew up in an immigrant home,

01:07:16.500 --> 01:07:18.410
I have internalized this idea

01:07:18.410 --> 01:07:24.200
that work is a very zero-some
game, or either you're working

01:07:24.200 --> 01:07:27.040
and you are strung out,

01:07:27.040 --> 01:07:30.350
or you are, if you're not
doing that or some form

01:07:30.350 --> 01:07:34.070
of that, then you are lazy.

01:07:34.070 --> 01:07:37.910
And I think just trying to
navigate, you know, those values

01:07:37.910 --> 01:07:40.080
about work and applying
them to creative life

01:07:40.080 --> 01:07:43.100
I found to be kind
of a messy process.

01:07:43.100 --> 01:07:47.560
So, I was wondering what each
of you had to say about that.

