I think it's important

01:07:55.930 --> 01:07:57.820
to consider it work.

01:07:57.820 --> 01:08:04.160
That it's just -- it's not just
like something that we are doing

01:08:04.160 --> 01:08:08.640
for fun, but it takes work
and it takes effort and time.

01:08:08.640 --> 01:08:10.970
But, also, I think there's a --

01:08:14.050 --> 01:08:16.200
I think it also takes like
being kind to yourself

01:08:16.200 --> 01:08:17.500
when it's not working out.

01:08:17.500 --> 01:08:19.980
I forgot -- oh God.

01:08:19.980 --> 01:08:21.960
Okay, this is going
to be so embarrassing.

01:08:21.960 --> 01:08:28.290
So, what is -- what is
the name of the woman

01:08:28.290 --> 01:08:30.820
who wrote Eat, Pray, Love?

01:08:30.820 --> 01:08:32.120
Elizabeth Gilbert.

01:08:32.120 --> 01:08:36.790
Well, I was watching one
of her Ted Talks [laughter]

01:08:36.790 --> 01:08:43.960
and my friend directed
me to her Ted Talk.

01:08:43.960 --> 01:08:46.080
And she talks about in
like, I think it was

01:08:46.080 --> 01:08:47.540
like Ancient Greece
they believed

01:08:47.540 --> 01:08:50.270
in the spirit of
the genius, right?

01:08:50.270 --> 01:08:56.160
And that [inaudible] and artists
weren't actually like geniuses

01:08:56.160 --> 01:08:59.600
or whatever, but they had
the spirit of a genius living

01:08:59.600 --> 01:09:01.250
in the walls of their studio.

01:09:01.250 --> 01:09:05.290
And, so, when they're in
their studio and they're ready

01:09:05.290 --> 01:09:09.120
to create, sometimes the genius
would come and use their body

01:09:09.120 --> 01:09:12.030
as a vessel to make art.

01:09:12.030 --> 01:09:15.070
And then when they're in their
studio and they're unable

01:09:15.070 --> 01:09:16.370
to create something,

01:09:16.370 --> 01:09:18.890
it's because the genius is
off somewhere else, right?

01:09:18.890 --> 01:09:22.400
And, so, that like takes away
the pressure of like I need

01:09:22.400 --> 01:09:24.590
to be like this working machine.

01:09:24.590 --> 01:09:26.290
I need to be -- or,
something is wrong

01:09:26.290 --> 01:09:27.590
with me if I'm not doing it.

01:09:27.590 --> 01:09:30.270
Why can't -- why can't I do it?

01:09:30.270 --> 01:09:31.680
And I like that idea.

01:09:31.680 --> 01:09:35.810
Thank you, Elizabeth
Gilbert [laughter].

01:09:35.810 --> 01:09:41.650
I also like the idea of
considering it work, too.

01:09:41.650 --> 01:09:47.580
So, the -- so, yeah,
so like there's --

01:09:51.070 --> 01:09:56.860
I find like when I
can't create something

01:09:56.860 --> 01:10:00.470
that I can edit something,
right,

01:10:00.470 --> 01:10:02.410
something that I created before.

01:10:02.410 --> 01:10:05.100
And I think that, yeah,
that's part of it.

01:10:05.100 --> 01:10:06.930
Like figuring out
where your energy goes

01:10:06.930 --> 01:10:13.040
if it can't go towards the
thing you want it to go to.

01:10:13.040 --> 01:10:14.340
&gt;&gt; R. O. Kwon: So,

01:10:14.340 --> 01:10:16.730
until December I had a very
consistent answer for this,

01:10:16.730 --> 01:10:18.490
because I did really write
pretty much every day

01:10:18.490 --> 01:10:19.790
for those 10 years.

01:10:19.790 --> 01:10:21.650
But, since December I've been
writing so little fiction,

01:10:21.650 --> 01:10:24.570
and if I'm not writing fiction
I feel a little dead inside,

01:10:24.570 --> 01:10:26.720
so I've been a little dead
inside for a little while.

01:10:26.720 --> 01:10:28.020
It's okay.

01:10:28.020 --> 01:10:29.320
It's okay.

01:10:29.320 --> 01:10:31.600
I soon will get it back.

01:10:31.600 --> 01:10:37.990
But, the -- so, until December I
had all kinds of rules in place.

01:10:37.990 --> 01:10:40.640
Like I did not have
internet during the day.

01:10:40.640 --> 01:10:41.940
I didn't have a flip phone.

01:10:41.940 --> 01:10:43.240
I've been borrowing a smartphone

01:10:43.240 --> 01:10:45.320
so I could get around
as I travel.

01:10:45.320 --> 01:10:48.570
I would not talk to anyone
in the morning before I got

01:10:48.570 --> 01:10:52.280
to work, because if I got to
writing because I didn't --

01:10:52.280 --> 01:10:53.740
I wanted to go as fast as I can

01:10:53.740 --> 01:10:56.240
from my dream state
to my writing.

01:10:56.240 --> 01:11:00.100
I wouldn't even eat until I had
gotten like a solid hour of work

01:11:00.100 --> 01:11:02.580
or so in, because
like I find food

01:11:02.580 --> 01:11:04.140
to be extremely pleasurable,

01:11:04.140 --> 01:11:05.440
and that's very distracting
[laughter]

01:11:05.440 --> 01:11:07.540
if I'm at home writing.

01:11:07.540 --> 01:11:10.020
I -- oh man, all kinds of shit.

01:11:10.020 --> 01:11:13.270
But, it's been less
useful lately,

01:11:13.270 --> 01:11:16.080
again because I've been doing
all this other kind of stuff,

01:11:16.080 --> 01:11:20.530
which I don't regret, but
it's not fiction writing.

01:11:20.530 --> 01:11:24.990
And, so, lately I've been taking
-- I'm on the extreme other end

01:11:24.990 --> 01:11:26.290
of trying to do things.

01:11:26.290 --> 01:11:28.990
Like at the very least on
a given trying to write

01:11:28.990 --> 01:11:31.040
for like five minutes
or 10 minutes.

01:11:31.040 --> 01:11:35.580
At the very least by trying to
-- at the very least trying --

01:11:35.580 --> 01:11:38.080
like if I notice a
word I want to use,

01:11:38.080 --> 01:11:39.430
like writing down that word.

01:11:39.430 --> 01:11:42.530
And, so just trying to stay in
touch in some way with a part

01:11:42.530 --> 01:11:44.550
of myself that loves fiction
and thrives on fiction

01:11:44.550 --> 01:11:47.400
and needs fiction to live.

01:11:47.400 --> 01:11:49.700
And so, yeah, I feel like
those are two ends of --

01:11:49.700 --> 01:11:53.610
two like very different
kinds of ends.

01:11:53.610 --> 01:11:54.910
First, there's the [inaudible].

01:11:54.910 --> 01:11:57.250
I was -- I was a -- you know,
I was like a hermit in a --

01:11:57.250 --> 01:11:59.060
hermit in the room answer,

01:11:59.060 --> 01:12:01.490
and then there's the I
barely have time to write.

01:12:01.490 --> 01:12:02.790
But, I'm trying.

01:12:02.790 --> 01:12:04.090
And I'm trying to stay in touch

01:12:04.090 --> 01:12:06.380
with it every day
to the extent I can.

